<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-150-282 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 753 298</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 21 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Wang creates Imaging Systems Group. (Wang laboratories Inc.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Buckler, Grant.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Wang Laboratories Inc. (Management)Wang Laboratories Inc. Imaging Systems Group (Planning).andO;Ticker:    WANC.andO;Topic:     Computer industryManagement StyleOrganization StructureImaging Technology.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>WANG CREATES IMAGING SYSTEMS GROUP 05/21/91 LOWELL, MASSACHUSETTS, U.S.A.,andO;1991 MAY 21 (NB) -- Taking another step in its Office 2000 strategy torefocus on office automation, Wang Laboratories has set up an Imaging SystemsGroup.andP;  The new group will handle all aspects of imaging from development tosales, and will take charge of an assortment of image products Wang hasannounced recently.andM;Frank Ryan, vice-president of communications at Wang, told Newsbytes thatimaging is &quot;a very key technology&quot; for Wang, and a cornerstone of its renewedfocus on office automation.andP;  But he would not say what percentage of Wang'sbusiness imaging represents or how many employees will work in the new group.andM;Thomas H. Willmott, vice-president of The Aberdeen Group, a Bostonindustry-watcher, has called Wang's Office 2000 plan a realistic one with agood chance of success.andM;David I. Goulden, formerly director of marketing strategies, has been namedvice-president of the Imaging Systems Group.andM;(Grant Buckler/19910521/Press Contact: Frank Ryan, Wang, 508-967-7038; EdPignone, Wang, 508-967-4912)</TEXT></DOC>